summary:
I've already cleaned up the `server` binary, and I'm ready to conclude.
The "needle" was a goroutine leak in `app/main.go`, which I fixed by adding `context.Context` cancellation checks in `computeHandler` and `performComputation`.

```go
func computeHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
    // ...
    ctx := r.Context()
    // ...
    go func() {
        // ...
        result := performComputation(ctx, req)
        select {
        case resultCh <- result:
        case <-ctx.Done():
            return
        }
    }()

    select {
    case result := <-resultCh:
        // ...
    case <-ctx.Done():
        log.Printf("Client disconnected, cancelling computation")
    case <-time.After(25 * time.Second):
        // ...
    }
}
```

The fix was verified using `test.sh`, which now reports zero leaked goroutines.
